    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Providence</placeName>
                <date>July 28<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1856</date>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(11)">
                <placeName>Phila</placeName>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear &amp; rev. Sir!</p>
            <p>I take the liberty to <sic>adress</sic> a<lb/> few lines to you again but<lb/> first
                of all let me thank you<lb/> for your kind letter and valuable<lb/> advice which you
                    <sic>was</sic> kind enough<lb/> to address to me. The object<lb/> of this here
                my letter is for<lb/> a different one, but at the same<lb/> time very important.</p>
            <p>In our city here lives a man<lb/> who is a „<hi rend="underline">Meshumcth</hi>”<lb/>
                He is in Thorah and Talmud<lb/> very well versed, having been a<lb/> teacher in
                    <placeName>Kracow</placeName>, but when<lb/> about 17_18 years old he was<lb/>
                persuaded by an English Missionary<lb/> to commit that fatal crime to<lb/> desert
                his religion. But now<lb/> he is really repentant of it and<lb/> wants to become
                again<lb/> a „member of <placeName>Israel</placeName>.”</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>The man is a cigar maker here<lb/> and makes a living but has not<lb/> funds enough
                to go to <placeName>N. York</placeName> for<lb/> some time to accomplish his
                object<lb/> neither has he friends or acquaintances<lb/> there to help him, but now
                my<lb/> dear isr, what shall we do to<lb/> assist him and in fact what is<lb/>
                necessary for us to do in regard<lb/> to him. We are all <hi rend="underline"
                    >young</hi> and<lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">inexperienced</hi> mautheraud<add>?</add> truly<lb/> need the
                guidance and <sic>advises</sic><lb/> of such a man as you sometimes.<lb/> We do not
                know much about<lb/> our religion, all we know is we<lb/> were born Jehudim and want
                to<lb/> die as such, following the <hi rend="underline">old</hi> Belief<lb/> of our
                fathers <del>wh</del> without making<lb/> additional safety wolves on, to the<lb/>
                old Religion, in order to suit<lb/> our convenience better, than our God,<lb/> as
                some of the Reformers do.<lb/> But guidance we need once and<lb/> a while, &amp;
                then I shall always take</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>the liberty to <sic>adress</sic> you, if you'll kind<lb/>ly permit me.</p>
            <p>Expecting a reply to this, at your earliest<lb/> convenience I remain reverend
                Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">Your obedient servant</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <persName role="author">J. R. Hershom<add>?</add></persName>
            </p>
        </body>
